{
  "stem": "5639.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Judenrat. ?] The nominal role of the Judenrat-- that's the officers of the elders of Jews-- was to keep order within ghetto, and to attend to all sorts of Jewish affairs-- burials, sicknesses, hunger, a location where to live, distribution of food, distribution of clothing for the poor, and so on.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So actually, it was more, officially, more a social role.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 76,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And very soon it developed into an arm of Gestapo.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 77,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, by giving them an order, tomorrow you have to deliver me 5,000 Jews.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 78,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And this is where the moral corruption--",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was not a question of being prepared.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[DRINKS] There was not a question of being prepared.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because by that time it became pretty obvious that the whole game was a game for survival.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the misconception was that if you work for the Germans, as long as they need you, your chance of survival is bigger.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 79,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And this is where the horrible thing settled in, the disease of corruption-- the disease that I have to survive and no matter what price.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because it was a disease of corruption.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You could bribe people to exempt you from certain tasks.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Jews had to clear snow.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Jews had to clear latrines.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You had a bit of money, you had a bit of connection, you went to the Jewish [GERMAN], to the Jewish council.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And you say, look, I pay for a poor man for two days' work.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Let him do the work.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There was nothing wrong with that sort of corruption, because by that time it was rather welcome.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But when you started to bribe the high officials, that's where the rot set in.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 80,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "As long as you bought yourself out, and you provided work for someone else, there was, perhaps, a bit of a moral justification.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
